rippa@netcom.com (Bruce Busby) writes:
>lesko@GOMEZ.phys.virginia.edu writes:

>>The front page of today's Washington Post (Monday, Jan 24)
>>has an article about the NSA's (relatively) new museum
>>located behind a Shell station in a defunct motel surrounded
>>by a chain-link fence just off the Baltimore-Washington Parkway.

>Would that be the remains of the old Colony 7?

Yes.  It is an interesting museum. I stopped by there a month or so back
and checked it out. While it is small, it has lots of machines with a
history. Even some old books dating back to the 1500s. The highlight of the
museum (IMO) is a real working Enigma machine.


